#include <iostream>
#include <string>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

class Player {
private:
    string name;
    int votes;

public:
    Player(string n) : name(n), votes(0) {}
    
    void addVote() { votes++; }
    string getName() const { return name; }
    int getVotes() const { return votes; }
    void setVotes(int v) { votes = v; }
};

class VotingSystem {
private:
    vector<Player> players;

public:
    void addPlayer(const string& name) {
        players.emplace_back(name);
        cout << "Player added: " << name << endl;
    }

    void vote(int index) {
        if (index >= 0 && index < players.size()) {
            players[index].addVote();
            cout << "Vote counted for: " << players[index].getName() << endl;
        } else {
            cout << "Invalid player index!" << endl;
        }
    }

    void showRankings() {
        sort(players.begin(), players.end(), [](const Player& a, const Player& b) {
            return a.getVotes() > b.getVotes();
        });

        int totalVotes = 0;
        for (const auto& player : players) {
            totalVotes += player.getVotes();
        }

        cout << "\n--- Player Rankings ---\n";
        for (size_t i = 0; i < players.size(); i++) {
            double percentage = (totalVotes == 0) ? 0 : (players[i].getVotes() * 100.0 / totalVotes);
            cout << i + 1 << ". " << players[i].getName()
                << " - " << players[i].getVotes() << " votes"
                << " (" << percentage << "% )" << endl;
        }
    }

    void listPlayers() {
        if (players.empty()) {
            cout << "No players added yet." << endl;
            return;
        }
        cout << "\nCurrent Players:\n";
        for (size_t i = 0; i < players.size(); i++) {
            cout << i + 1 << ") " << players[i].getName() << endl;
        }
    }
};

int main() {
    VotingSystem system;
    int choice;

    while (true) {
        cout << "\n===== Ballon d'Or Voting Menu =====\n";
        cout << "1. Add Player\n2. Vote\n3. Show Rankings\n4. List Players\n0. Exit\n";
        cout << "Choose an option: ";

        if (!(cin >> choice)) {
            cin.clear();
            cin.ignore(10000, '\n');
            cout << "Please enter a valid number." << endl;
            continue;
        }

        cin.ignore(10000, '\n');

        if (choice == 0) break;

        switch (choice) {
        case 1: {
            string name;
            cout << "Enter player name: ";
            getline(cin, name);
            if (!name.empty()) system.addPlayer(name);
            else cout << "Name cannot be empty." << endl;
            break;
        }
        case 2: {
            system.listPlayers();
            int index;
            cout << "Enter player index to vote for: ";
            if (cin >> index) system.vote(index - 1);
            else {
                cin.clear();
                cin.ignore(10000, '\n');
                cout << "Invalid input." << endl;
            }
            break;
        }
        case 3:
            system.showRankings();
            break;
        case 4:
            system.listPlayers();
            break;
        default:
            cout << "Invalid choice!" << endl;
        }
    }

    cout << "\nThank you for using the Ballon d'Or Voting System!" << endl;
    return 0;
}
